            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1351005541,
            "creation_date": 1351005541,
            "body": "<p>This 8 digit number appears to be specific to WebSphere logs. They might correspond to the error codes on this page: <a href=\"http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/tsminfo/v6/index.jsp?topic=%2Fcom.ibm.itsm.tshoot.doc%2Fr_pdg_retcodes.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/tsminfo/v6/index.jsp?topic=%2Fcom.ibm.itsm.tshoot.doc%2Fr_pdg_retcodes.html<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>In which case 00000066 would be a keyfile i/o error.<\/p>\n\n<p>Or, it could be a line number. That is a rather logical place to put the line number. I searched other similar 8 digit codes and some of them did not correspond to the above error codes.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 13033783,
            "question_id": 13033142
        }
